assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Integrated Holding Company K.S.C.P. operates in the logistics industry in Kuwait and internationally. It offers equipment leasing and hiring services; heavy lifting services, including specialized lifting services, and engineering and rigging services; heavy transport haulage services, such as various trucks, trailers, and equipment; and alternative lift services comprising gantry system, and jacking and skidding services. The company also provides earth moving services, which include demolition and construction activities; industrial equipment services, which include air compressors, welding machines, tower lights, man lifts, and tele handlers; and rig move services that comprise drilling rig and super rig move, work over, casing, and heavy haulage. In addition, it offers power rentals services for temporary project location, including generators, transformers, fuel tanks, load banks, synchronizers, and totals panels; shutdown management services; and tower cranes for residential and commercial, civil construction, building infrastructure, bridges and flyovers, and other construction projects. Further, the company provides port operations services, such as handling of aggregates, pet coke, clinker, gypsum rocks, coal, steel scrap, direct reduced iron, hot briquetted iron, general cargo, and jumbo bags; and other services that include hopper system, weigh bridge operation, and port information management services. Integrated Holding Company K.S.C.P. was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Kuwait City, Kuwait.
